*waves from her lifeboat* Bye, Livejournal! *screams at the shore grows further and further away* I never really got into using your service! The site was always down! *cups her hands over her mouth and shouts* I'm getting my own freakin' journal noooowwwww!

*pokes journal* I've been neglecting this thing. Well, I've been neglecting a lot of things, unless they relate to school. I simply don't have time. *cries* This is horrible. *beats school ferociously with a stick* As if there aren't enough emotional traumas being wreaked on the world as well right now. *sigh* Yeah...

Well, hell, thought I'd pop in. Scrawl down a little, because I want to. But only oh-so-briefly, because I have an utterly amazing shitload of things to do this weekend. *shakes her head* Something's gonna snap. I don't know what yet. But something's gotta.

~ the wench herself
http://kitchenwench.livejournal.com/2202.html

Oh, I'm just a sheep, stealin' this quiz from Implet. Though, frankly, she is right about chapstick sounding dirty...

7 things I am afraid of:
1. family and friends dying
2. my own imagination
3. being a failure
4. hurting people
5. the dark
6. people without morals
7. death

7 things that make me laugh:
1. my friends
2. Danielle's bizarre dreams
3. my dad
4. Varun
5. "Whose Line Is it Anyway?"
6. play practice
7. high quality bad-fic

7 things that make me cry:
1. movies
2. sappy commercials on tv
3. "Touched By an Angel" episodes (shut up!)
4. my dad
5. Jeff Buckley's voice
6. being too hard on myself
7. Christian Bale's hotness combined with the fact that he's married

7 things I love:
1. iced carmel machiatos from Starbucks
2. travel and fine cuisine
3. my dog
4. family
5. friends
6. reading and writing
7. music
(like they expect you to list just seven...)

7 things I don't understand:
1. men
2. myself
3. chemical bonds
4. low self-esteem
5. intolerance
6. cruelty to animals
7. people without morals

7 things on my desk:
1. can of Blue Sky Cherry Vanilla Creme soda
2. Fiske guide to colleges 2001 ed.
3. large green rubber caterpillar
4. Rufus Wainwright (my Dell computer system)
5. cd case and player
6. pile of photo cds
7. tv remote

7 facts about myself:
1. I like to buff my fingernails
2. I have gray hairs at seventeen
3. I have a birthmark under my chin
4. I wear seven different silver rings on my fingers
5. I have bad posture
6. I'm (virtually, if not actually) legally blind without glasses or contacts
7. my thumbs are double jointed, but nothing else is

7 things to do before I die:
1. learn how to stop being so hard on myself
2. get married
3. become successful at a job I love
4. learn to cook as well as my dad and grandmother
5. learn Italian, French, Spanish, and Chinese (Mandarin and Cantonese)
6. meet David Foster Wallace
7. have my photo on a billboard in Hong Kong advertising skin care products
http://kitchenwench.livejournal.com/1890.html

Husking Bee rawks. This is the best Japanese music I've heard. (Okay, so the only Japanese bands I've heard are Cibo Matto, Pizzacato Five, and Yoko Ono...) Still. "A Small Potato's Mind" is awesome. I haven't a clue why it's called that or what they say during the song, but who gives a rip.

So, I got my schedule from school in the mail today. It's pretty damn awesome (English first hour? Second hour Ceramics? I don't have to even think till 4th hour.) except I don't have a free hour first semester and that simply won't do. So I'll have to either drop or switch something, but that's okay.

In other news: Hung out with the old people today and am nearing the completion of my France page. As for Crime and Punishment... going nowhere fast. *grins*

~ the wench herself
http://kitchenwench.livejournal.com/1573.html

*scowls* *has so much bloody shit to take care of before tomorrow, before the end of this week, before schools starts, before...* *starts sobbing and falls over*

But good news. Al Sharpton might run for president. So now it's all okay. *tears at her hair*

You lucky folks. I went to the grocery store again. I didn't have a list; it was just to buy lunch, which is a bad time to go grocery shopping because you're hungry and, well, everything looks appealing. Some purchasing highlights include:

  • cinnamon bread
  • more mandarin-lime juice spritzers
  • Leann Chin chicken wings
  • sushi
  • nasty carrot juice for my mom
  • sundried tomato and balsamic vinegar potato chips
  • mixed organic greens salad w/chicken and raspberry vinaigrette
  • grilled sandwich
  • peaches and nectarines and cherries
See. Look at that. So much food. *shakes her head* *sighs heavily and wanders off to do sucky web junk for the old people place she volunteers at*
~the wench herself
http://kitchenwench.livejournal.com/1511.html

Fine. I see how it is. None of you care about my personal life; all you want is my GROCERY LIST! Well, fine, if that's how it's gonna be...
Grocery List
  • organic cheese curls
  • juice and/or fruity-type pop
  • carrot chips
  • tea
  • bread
  • cereal
  • white peaches
  • soy milk
Also, now featuring...
Toiletries List
  • Clean and Clear face wash and astringent
  • emery board
  • Eliz. Arden Green Tea perfume
  • green tea shampoo
  • Biore oil-free moisturizer
  • eye drops
Man. Ya'll are just darn lucky I went shopping today. *grins*
~the wench herself

*mashes her face into the keyboard* I just spent the last 2+ hours without power. Stupid NSP. Actually, they got bought over. Now they're Excel Energy. But whatever. This is a moot point.

Anyway, I don't know how people did it back in the day. I was so bored, I actually read more of Crime and Punishment. In fact, I was in the middle of updating my LJ when suddenly my screen flickered and everything went black and the I cried. So, yes, this is why I return, except forgot what it was that I was updating, so I say, Heck, let's post another entry because Imp would read my grocery list. *grins*

~ the wench herself
http://kitchenwench.livejournal.com/1004.html

I just read fifty pages of Crime and Punishment in a sitting. And it truly was criminal, not to mention punishment. *whimpers b/c her Rufus' keyboard is sticky* So I finally fixed the layout on the Royalty LJ as much as one possibly can, given the constraints of this service. *shrugs*

*goes to deal with email and her slowly growing France travelogue*

~ the wench herself

*personally thinks her color scheme is pretty sexy and should therefore have a theme named after it, esp. since some of those themes are ugly* Laaa. I... always swore I'd never put my diary online. In fact, I probably still won't. What exactly I plan to do with this is still beyond me, but, gosh, it sure was fun playing with the colors... Also, look how nicely those kittens coordinate with my colors! (And I don't even like kittens...)
~ the wench herself
